The <b>Bentley-Ottmann algorithm</b> is a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../856/8700856.xml">
sweep line algorithm</link> for solving the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../098/3194098.xml">
line segment intersection</link> problem on a plane. It works by considering the intersections of the line segments with a "sweep" line which is moved progressively across the set of line segments.
